div.div: Please refer to FAQ to learn how to update your manager, direct reports, matrix reports and non-employee reports

div.style: padding:1px 1px 1px 5px; font-size:8pt; color:Black; border:solid 2px #CFEAF9; background-color:#FFFFDB; text-align:left;

font.div: Business Contact is the Citigroup employee who is the primary contact for the non-employee and will perform all entitlement reviews.

font.span: This person has no direct reports.
This person has no matrix reports.

span.title: The People-Based tree is based on Direct Manager-to-Employee relationships.

font.span: *Non-Employees do not have a manager-to-non-employee relationship in the people-based tree.

span.title: Managed Segment replaces CBOH as the standard Business Organization Hierarchy of Citi. Managed Segment is split into Citicorp and Citi Holdings at the top levels, and each individual business defines the lower level structures of the hierarchy.

div.style: padding:1px 1px 1px 5px; font-size:8pt; color:Black; border:solid 2px #CFEAF9; background-color:#FFFFDB; text-align:left; display:none;

td.div: This is the Global Organizational Code (GOC) the worker reports to. The lowest-level CBOH node may contain multiple GOCs.

span.title: The Managed Geography allows the mapping of a GOC to the geography from which it is managed, even if that geography differs from where the GOC's staff and/or financials are physically located.
